<TITLE> New banking division gets nod </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 21 (bdnews24.com)A cabinet division meeting has approved a ministry of finance proposal to establish a separate banking division to be headed by a secretary. This approval was given Monday at the meeting of the secretary-committee on administrative affairs, presided over by cabinet secretary Md Abdul Aziz. An official who attended said the finance ministry proposal was approved in principle. He said the new division was set to be manned by a staff of 82. Of the total, 15 posts have been decided. The new division will have a secretary, one joint secretary, 13 deputy and senior assistant secretaries. With the decision coming into effect, there will be three separate divisions under the finance ministry. The existing two are the finance division and internal resources division. Though the affairs relating to local banks and financial institutions will come under the purview of the new division, matters of international banking and financial institutions will be dealt with by the finance secretary. b
